WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.637 --> 00:00:05.773
- <i>Previously on Marshals...</i>
- We got to hold

2
00:00:05.839 --> 00:00:07.041
on what we got.

3
00:00:07.141 --> 00:00:08.042
We don't move.
it's Roner all over.

4
00:00:09.643 --> 00:00:10.711
Said you'd been experiencing

5
00:00:10.811 --> 00:00:12.513
some neck and shoulder pain?

6
00:00:12.646 --> 00:00:15.149
We'll run some tests.
try to find you some answers.

7
00:00:15.249 --> 00:00:16.484
Would you like to go
on a date sometime?

8
00:00:16.584 --> 00:00:17.818
I'd love to.

9
00:00:17.885 --> 00:00:19.287
Family name doesn't
carry water anymore.

10
00:00:19.353 --> 00:00:21.722
so you got to hide
behind a federal badge?

11
00:00:23.357 --> 00:00:24.692
This...

12
00:00:24.792 --> 00:00:28.129
- is a terrible idea.
- Long day.

13
00:01:26.354 --> 00:01:29.021
Winter fields came in nice.

14
00:01:29.123 --> 00:01:32.092
Yeah. Tom Weaver's hands
get all the credit.

15
00:01:32.193 --> 00:01:34.828
His daughter's hands
get credit. too?

16
00:01:35.628 --> 00:01:37.798
Hey. you communicating
with aliens?

17
00:01:37.898 --> 00:01:40.934
'Cause these hay bales
can't be for decoration. right?

18
00:01:41.068 --> 00:01:42.436
They're to feed the herd.

19
00:01:42.536 --> 00:01:44.405
Grass gets scarce
when the snow comes in.

20
00:01:44.505 --> 00:01:47.039
Get your hand warmers
ready. city slicker.

21
00:01:47.140 --> 00:01:48.476
Winter's coming.

22
00:01:48.609 --> 00:01:49.676
It's the first time
someone from Omaha's

23
00:01:49.777 --> 00:01:51.212
been slapped with that label.

24
00:01:51.312 --> 00:01:54.548
But I have you know. Tate.
I was freezing my ass off

25
00:01:54.648 --> 00:01:56.550
in the Hindu Kush when you
were still in diapers.

26
00:01:57.685 --> 00:02:00.488
Supposed to meet up with Deebo.

27
00:02:00.621 --> 00:02:02.423
Unless you got more grass
you want to stare at?

28
00:02:02.523 --> 00:02:04.892
Get out of here.

29
00:02:08.596 --> 00:02:11.332
Man. it's nice to see you two
doing so well.

30
00:02:12.433 --> 00:02:14.168
You know.
being a father suits you.

31
00:02:14.268 --> 00:02:16.304
Didn't come natural.

32
00:02:17.438 --> 00:02:19.307
I thought being somebody's son
would be the hardest thing

33
00:02:19.407 --> 00:02:21.041
I ever had to deal with.

34
00:02:22.510 --> 00:02:26.980
Man. I needed a morning
like this. Thank you. Coyo.

35
00:02:27.079 --> 00:02:28.482
Everything good?

36
00:02:28.582 --> 00:02:32.386
Yeah. just fighting battles
on multiple fronts. but

37
00:02:32.486 --> 00:02:34.288
it's nice to know
you got my six.

38
00:02:35.189 --> 00:02:37.691
Sketchy guy coming up
the driveway to the house.

39
00:02:57.478 --> 00:02:59.012
You lost?

40
00:02:59.112 --> 00:03:02.483
Not if I'm trying to figure out
where all the cowboys have gone.

41
00:03:02.583 --> 00:03:04.952
Think you can back up
that smart talk

42
00:03:05.018 --> 00:03:06.654
armed only with that six string?

43
00:03:06.720 --> 00:03:10.858
Ain't you heard?
I was born dangerous. Coyo.

44
00:03:19.166 --> 00:03:20.701
Damn. Double G.

45
00:03:20.801 --> 00:03:24.572
- I ain't seen you since...
- Camp Uhley. Afghanistan.

46
00:03:24.704 --> 00:03:25.873
So. after all this time.

47
00:03:25.973 --> 00:03:27.308
you just figured
you'd show up in Montana

48
00:03:27.375 --> 00:03:28.709
unannounced. huh?

49
00:03:28.841 --> 00:03:30.811
Well.
felt a calling to head west.

50
00:03:30.878 --> 00:03:33.314
see how my old teammate
was doing.

51
00:03:34.281 --> 00:03:36.350
Good Lord. is that Tate?

52
00:03:36.417 --> 00:03:37.985
Hey. Tate.

53
00:03:38.085 --> 00:03:39.820
I want you to meet Garrett. He's
my old buddy from the Teams.

54
00:03:39.887 --> 00:03:41.389
Figured.

55
00:03:41.489 --> 00:03:43.891
Can't imagine anyone else
getting a greeting like that.

56
00:03:47.027 --> 00:03:50.063
Cal? Wasn't expecting
to see you.

57
00:03:50.163 --> 00:03:53.867
Double G. In the flesh.

58
00:03:54.668 --> 00:03:57.671
I guess I should start
believing in ghosts.

59
00:04:00.107 --> 00:04:01.442
You were all teammates?

60
00:04:01.575 --> 00:04:03.911
Three-quarters of a badass group
of pipe hitters

61
00:04:04.011 --> 00:04:06.514
everybody called
the Four Musketeers.

62
00:04:06.614 --> 00:04:08.616
Nobody called us that.

63
00:04:09.450 --> 00:04:10.484
Who's the fourth?

64
00:04:16.223 --> 00:04:17.925
Let's. uh.
get your stuff inside.

65
00:04:18.024 --> 00:04:19.760
There's a lot to catch up on.
Ain't that right. Cal?

66
00:04:19.893 --> 00:04:24.264
I got something back at work.
It's good seeing you. Double G.

67
00:04:24.365 --> 00:04:25.766
Come on.

68
00:04:25.899 --> 00:04:28.936
Sure thing. boss.

69
00:04:29.903 --> 00:04:31.839
Get you inside. man.

70
00:05:15.916 --> 00:05:18.486
Hey. The fugitive

71
00:05:18.619 --> 00:05:21.489
we collared yesterday
was processed in Helena.

72
00:05:21.622 --> 00:05:23.391
And?

73
00:05:24.157 --> 00:05:26.226
And I thought
you'd want to know.

74
00:05:26.326 --> 00:05:28.929
Now I do. Thanks.

75
00:05:30.998 --> 00:05:32.199
You feeling okay?

76
00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:34.301
Yeah. yeah. Why wouldn't I be?

77
00:05:34.368 --> 00:05:38.539
Jared said your run-in was at
the doctor's office parking lot.

78
00:05:38.639 --> 00:05:42.275
- You left that detail out.
- I'm fine.

79
00:05:42.342 --> 00:05:44.177
Okay.

80
00:05:48.148 --> 00:05:49.750
Are we?

81
00:05:52.453 --> 00:05:55.155
We both agreed we made
a mistake and. you know.

82
00:05:55.255 --> 00:05:57.324
gonna respect boundaries
at work.

83
00:05:57.425 --> 00:05:58.926
Stay front-sight focused.

84
00:06:01.595 --> 00:06:02.896
It's nothing personal.

85
00:06:02.996 --> 00:06:05.365
Yeah. no. nothing personal.

86
00:06:07.401 --> 00:06:08.702
Right.

87
00:06:11.705 --> 00:06:14.908
Down.
Down. down. down. Good. Good.

88
00:06:15.042 --> 00:06:16.677
That horse has a fire
in his belly.

89
00:06:16.744 --> 00:06:19.046
I'd sooner jump on a grenade
than mess with him.

90
00:06:19.146 --> 00:06:21.314
Yeah.
he's got a temper for sure.

91
00:06:22.215 --> 00:06:24.652
I guess I would too if somebody
was trying to take my freedom.

92
00:06:24.718 --> 00:06:27.387
Well. I wish somebody
would've gave us this much TLC

93
00:06:27.488 --> 00:06:29.056
when we got out of the sandbox.

94
00:06:29.156 --> 00:06:32.426
All right. Come on. Come on.

95
00:06:38.532 --> 00:06:39.733
Good.

96
00:06:42.936 --> 00:06:46.173
I guess nobody gets off easy
getting out of the Teams.

97
00:06:46.239 --> 00:06:48.408
You had it worse than most.

98
00:06:49.643 --> 00:06:51.812
I look like I'm gonna
suck start my pistol to you?

99
00:06:51.912 --> 00:06:54.147
Just haven't seen you
in a decade.

100
00:06:55.148 --> 00:06:57.651
You were spinning out
pretty good last time I did.

101
00:06:58.819 --> 00:07:01.622
I ain't got a worry
in the world. Coyo.

102
00:07:01.722 --> 00:07:03.924
Trading in that rifle
for a guitar

103
00:07:04.057 --> 00:07:05.693
was the best decision
I ever made.

104
00:07:06.426 --> 00:07:08.962
Always did like
hearing you play that thing.

105
00:07:09.062 --> 00:07:12.132
I've been making a name
for myself up in Nashville. too.

106
00:07:13.867 --> 00:07:17.304
Glad you left the past
in the sandbox. brother.

107
00:07:17.404 --> 00:07:19.106
No looking
in the rearview for me.

108
00:07:19.206 --> 00:07:21.274
Music's my purpose.

109
00:07:21.408 --> 00:07:23.844
Seems you and old Cal
found a new one. too.

110
00:07:25.345 --> 00:07:28.081
I was spinning my wheels till
he offered me a Marshal badge.

111
00:07:28.181 --> 00:07:31.985
Ain't that rich.

112
00:07:32.119 --> 00:07:36.089
Cal gives you a new career.
and he ended mine.

113
00:07:39.292 --> 00:07:42.530
Well. all this reminiscing's
making me thirsty.

114
00:07:54.975 --> 00:07:56.544
Well. you know.

115
00:07:56.644 --> 00:07:59.179
only ten percent of first dates
make it to the third.

116
00:07:59.279 --> 00:08:02.516
Good for us.
beating the odds already.

117
00:08:03.350 --> 00:08:06.086
We got to survive
our fourth date

118
00:08:06.186 --> 00:08:10.190
before "us" makes it
into our vernacular.

119
00:08:10.323 --> 00:08:13.160
Not to get ahead
of anything. but. uh.

120
00:08:13.293 --> 00:08:15.328
are you thinking
about telling Cal?

121
00:08:16.329 --> 00:08:18.532
The man's got no say in my life.

122
00:08:19.332 --> 00:08:21.134
But he does in mine.

123
00:08:24.504 --> 00:08:26.339
Fine. How about now?

124
00:08:31.511 --> 00:08:34.280
- He just walked in. didn't he?
- Wait.

125
00:08:34.381 --> 00:08:36.616
So this is a-a thing?

126
00:08:40.721 --> 00:08:42.623
You got nothing to say?

127
00:08:43.557 --> 00:08:46.560
I didn't realize she was your
daughter when I asked her out.

128
00:08:47.828 --> 00:08:49.863
It's not something
I boast about.

129
00:08:58.138 --> 00:08:59.472
Enjoy your evenings.

130
00:09:09.382 --> 00:09:10.918
That charcoal filter.

131
00:09:11.018 --> 00:09:13.253
that's what makes it
Tennessee whiskey.

132
00:09:13.386 --> 00:09:15.388
Why are you pimping
Tennessee so hard?

133
00:09:15.488 --> 00:09:16.924
You said you were from Alabama.

134
00:09:17.057 --> 00:09:18.726
Well. I am.

135
00:09:18.826 --> 00:09:21.194
Only good thing
to come out of there is I-20.

136
00:09:21.294 --> 00:09:23.096
Myself included.

137
00:09:23.230 --> 00:09:25.332
I had to drag you out here
last week.

138
00:09:25.398 --> 00:09:27.134
now you're just
a regular. cowboy?

139
00:09:27.234 --> 00:09:28.869
I'm just playing tour guide.

140
00:09:28.936 --> 00:09:31.805
Garrett didn't appreciate the
peace and quiet at the ranch.

141
00:09:31.905 --> 00:09:33.941
Ugh. I get it.
I can't wait to get back

142
00:09:34.074 --> 00:09:36.043
to the concrete jungle myself.

143
00:09:36.143 --> 00:09:38.245
Fresh air is too suffocating.

144
00:09:38.345 --> 00:09:40.347
You know. I think you just
gave me my next song title.

145
00:09:40.413 --> 00:09:42.915
And that makes you my muse.

146
00:09:43.016 --> 00:09:44.384
You know.
last time I heard you play.

147
00:09:44.451 --> 00:09:46.954
you were interrupted
by a mortar attack.

148
00:09:47.721 --> 00:09:50.023
Taliban's a tough crowd. huh?

149
00:09:50.123 --> 00:09:51.524
They ain't got nothing
on those dive bars

150
00:09:51.625 --> 00:09:52.693
I've played down south. though.

151
00:09:52.793 --> 00:09:54.094
The stage is right there.

152
00:09:54.194 --> 00:09:56.029
You can finish
what you started for Kayce.

153
00:09:56.096 --> 00:09:59.199
I only play big venues
now. darling.

154
00:10:01.802 --> 00:10:05.472
Hey. Pull up a chair. Cal.
I'm buying.

155
00:10:07.908 --> 00:10:09.643
I think I'm gonna rain check it.

156
00:10:09.777 --> 00:10:11.144
After all we've been through.

157
00:10:11.244 --> 00:10:12.846
you can't sit down.
have one drink with me?

158
00:10:16.549 --> 00:10:17.851
Yeah. you know what?

159
00:10:17.951 --> 00:10:22.790
Next round. and the round
after that. is on me.

160
00:10:22.890 --> 00:10:24.725
Okay? Enjoy your night.

161
00:10:24.825 --> 00:10:26.960
Hooyah. Senior Chief.

162
00:10:30.030 --> 00:10:33.500
Well. here's to Two Musketeers.

163
00:10:33.600 --> 00:10:34.868
Cheers.

164
00:10:43.343 --> 00:10:45.012
Hey.

165
00:10:45.145 --> 00:10:48.615
Double G have you
howling at the moon last night?

166
00:10:48.682 --> 00:10:52.652
Took all my frogman skills just
to get him out of the Bullet.

167
00:10:52.753 --> 00:10:54.722
How is he?

168
00:10:55.989 --> 00:10:57.790
He's better than I expected.

169
00:10:57.891 --> 00:10:59.760
Seems to be all in
on this music thing.

170
00:10:59.860 --> 00:11:02.162
I mean. if he says so.

171
00:11:02.996 --> 00:11:05.598
Man shows up out of the blue.
after a decade.

172
00:11:05.665 --> 00:11:07.100
'cause life is good?

173
00:11:07.167 --> 00:11:08.501
Come on.

174
00:11:08.601 --> 00:11:10.103
I know a damaged frogman
when I see one.

175
00:11:10.203 --> 00:11:11.338
You should.

176
00:11:12.172 --> 00:11:14.207
You caused a lot of his damage.

177
00:11:26.720 --> 00:11:29.156
Hey. Tip just came in.

178
00:11:29.222 --> 00:11:31.992
Fugitive on our
Top 15 Most Wanted list.

179
00:11:32.059 --> 00:11:34.661
- Reed Pollard.
- Wait.

180
00:11:34.762 --> 00:11:37.664
The most wanted bank robber of
his generation is in our town?

181
00:11:37.731 --> 00:11:39.332
Planning his next heist.

182
00:11:39.399 --> 00:11:41.201
We got a possible
location on him.

183
00:11:41.301 --> 00:11:42.903
Yeah. I mean. Pollard's
been on the board for years.

184
00:11:43.003 --> 00:11:44.537
No one's come close
to catching him.

185
00:11:44.637 --> 00:11:47.607
Yeah. well. he's never been
on our hunting ground.

186
00:11:48.441 --> 00:11:50.010
Okay. Let's roll him up.

187
00:11:57.050 --> 00:11:58.585
Despite pulling off
some of the biggest heists

188
00:11:58.685 --> 00:11:59.753
of the last decade.
Pollard has managed to stay

189
00:11:59.887 --> 00:12:01.088
one step ahead of the Marshals.

190
00:12:01.221 --> 00:12:02.722
Yeah. this guy's
a modern-day Dillinger.

191
00:12:02.823 --> 00:12:04.758
His scores have netted millions.

192
00:12:04.858 --> 00:12:06.426
So what brings him to Montana?

193
00:12:06.559 --> 00:12:09.496
An anonymous tip says he's in
town scouting his next takedown.

194
00:12:09.562 --> 00:12:11.865
Bagging one of our most wanted.
that'd be a great way

195
00:12:11.965 --> 00:12:13.233
to start this day. y'all.

196
00:12:13.333 --> 00:12:14.935
- What's his target?
- We don't know.

197
00:12:15.035 --> 00:12:17.070
just that he's holed up
at the Ashford Rodeo Grounds.

198
00:12:17.204 --> 00:12:20.273
Rodeos have moved south for the
winter. Place will be deserted.

199
00:12:20.407 --> 00:12:21.674
Great. no civvies.

200
00:12:21.775 --> 00:12:23.443
Should we gear up.
full battle rattle?

201
00:12:23.576 --> 00:12:25.913
Pollard's not one to waste time.
so if he's moving on his target.

202
00:12:26.013 --> 00:12:27.447
I need you and Miles here.
quarterbacking.

203
00:12:27.547 --> 00:12:29.582
And. Andrea. you and Kayce.
you roll with me.

204
00:12:29.682 --> 00:12:31.018
Okay? Let's move.

205
00:12:33.620 --> 00:12:35.455
Did we just get benched?

206
00:12:35.588 --> 00:12:38.025
Sure feels like it.

207
00:12:38.125 --> 00:12:39.192
What'd you do?

208
00:12:39.292 --> 00:12:42.362
Nothing. You?

209
00:12:42.462 --> 00:12:44.031
Nothing.

210
00:12:44.131 --> 00:12:45.365
They're kicking doors.

211
00:12:45.465 --> 00:12:47.935
We're gonna get stuck here
doing paperwork.

212
00:12:51.972 --> 00:12:53.974
Nothing personal.

213
00:12:56.509 --> 00:12:57.710
Must have an inside connection

214
00:12:57.777 --> 00:12:59.446
to be holed up
in a place like this.

215
00:12:59.546 --> 00:13:01.114
Guy's stolen millions and
chooses to live like an animal?

216
00:13:01.248 --> 00:13:03.450
Lives like an animal
so he can steal millions.

217
00:13:03.583 --> 00:13:05.118
It's that kind
of discipline is why

218
00:13:05.218 --> 00:13:06.586
no one's come close
to catching him.

219
00:13:06.686 --> 00:13:08.121
How we want to do this?

220
00:13:08.221 --> 00:13:09.489
Pollard's known
for stealth. not force.

221
00:13:09.622 --> 00:13:11.491
so I think fast and dirty
should do it.

222
00:13:11.624 --> 00:13:13.160
Any word on his team?

223
00:13:13.293 --> 00:13:17.064
Usually only works with a few.
but n-never the same ones.

224
00:13:17.164 --> 00:13:18.999
Tip might be from
a scorned old crew member

225
00:13:19.132 --> 00:13:20.467
who's come back to haunt him.

226
00:13:20.567 --> 00:13:22.502
- Lot of that going around.
- Hey. Movement.

227
00:13:25.172 --> 00:13:26.173
On me.

228
00:13:34.481 --> 00:13:36.683
Federal agents. Show yourself!

229
00:14:07.814 --> 00:14:08.781
Contact rear!

230
00:14:17.424 --> 00:14:18.926
Go.

231
00:14:31.038 --> 00:14:32.940
Okay. hold fire.

232
00:14:33.040 --> 00:14:34.707
Check these bodies.

233
00:14:34.807 --> 00:14:36.243
U.S. Marshal!

234
00:14:40.747 --> 00:14:42.649
Kayce.
none of these guys are Pollard.

235
00:14:42.749 --> 00:14:44.317
It's got to be yours.

236
00:15:31.631 --> 00:15:34.234
Okay. Kayce and Andrea
are on the ground. searching.

237
00:15:34.334 --> 00:15:35.735
Where are we on Pollard?

238
00:15:35.835 --> 00:15:37.604
Local PD set up roadblocks.
three-mile perimeter.

239
00:15:37.704 --> 00:15:39.739
- Anything pop?
- No hits on the BOLO

240
00:15:39.839 --> 00:15:41.374
or at the perimeter checkpoints.

241
00:15:41.474 --> 00:15:42.909
Kayce says he clipped him.

242
00:15:42.976 --> 00:15:45.112
Have we checked hospitals.
local clinics?

243
00:15:45.245 --> 00:15:47.047
No gunshot wounds reported
anywhere within 30 miles.

244
00:15:47.147 --> 00:15:50.950
Gifford's gonna eat my lunch
if Bozeman PD get this collar.

245
00:15:51.051 --> 00:15:54.587
Did our fairy tipster happen
to come in with any more intel?

246
00:15:54.654 --> 00:15:56.656
He's gone radio silent.

247
00:15:56.756 --> 00:15:58.290
Okay. extend
to a statewide search

248
00:15:58.425 --> 00:16:00.760
'cause Pollard could've
stolen a car. slipped the net.

249
00:16:00.827 --> 00:16:02.462
- We can't lose him.
- Did you get anything

250
00:16:02.595 --> 00:16:04.464
from the three dead guys
you dropped?

251
00:16:04.597 --> 00:16:05.765
Still waiting on local PD

252
00:16:05.865 --> 00:16:07.234
to ID the guys

253
00:16:07.334 --> 00:16:09.569
'cause they were only carrying
guns and zip ties.

254
00:16:09.669 --> 00:16:12.872
Zip ties were likely
for hostages on their target.

255
00:16:12.972 --> 00:16:14.341
You may have
put them down right as

256
00:16:14.441 --> 00:16:15.675
they were launching their heist.

257
00:16:15.808 --> 00:16:17.110
Didn't put 'em all down.

258
00:16:17.177 --> 00:16:19.779
Yeah. don't remind me.

259
00:16:19.846 --> 00:16:21.414
And Pollard's the headliner
of this crew.

260
00:16:21.514 --> 00:16:24.917
It's unlike this team
to let such a big fish get away.

261
00:16:24.984 --> 00:16:26.586
Kicked the door
with a full unit.

262
00:16:26.653 --> 00:16:27.854
might've turned out different.

263
00:16:27.954 --> 00:16:30.490
Or maybe one of you
catches a round.

264
00:16:31.624 --> 00:16:33.193
You questioning my call?

265
00:16:33.293 --> 00:16:37.164
Not your call. your motive.

266
00:16:38.065 --> 00:16:40.267
My motive is to do
what's best for my team.

267
00:16:40.333 --> 00:16:42.335
and if you feel differently.

268
00:16:42.435 --> 00:16:44.104
that's on you.

269
00:16:44.871 --> 00:16:47.474
Now. we have a fugitive
on the loose.

270
00:16:48.875 --> 00:16:50.743
So. find him.

271
00:16:54.013 --> 00:16:55.148
Hey.

272
00:17:01.321 --> 00:17:03.690
Are you part
of this whole conspiracy?

273
00:17:03.790 --> 00:17:05.092
Oh. no. Man. no.

274
00:17:05.192 --> 00:17:08.694
The conspiracy to sideline me.
that's all you.

275
00:17:08.795 --> 00:17:12.598
I'm talking about
Miles and Maddie.

276
00:17:14.434 --> 00:17:18.171
They're... dating.
or whatever people do nowadays.

277
00:17:18.238 --> 00:17:21.174
Maddie's the girl
Miles had a crush on?

278
00:17:21.241 --> 00:17:24.977
Oh. Well. that explains
your grumpiness.

279
00:17:25.778 --> 00:17:27.114
At least towards him.

280
00:17:27.214 --> 00:17:28.748
Dating somebody I work with.

281
00:17:28.848 --> 00:17:30.383
Maddie's sticking it
to me. right?

282
00:17:30.483 --> 00:17:34.787
Sorry. it's... it's not
respecting work boundaries.

283
00:17:36.289 --> 00:17:38.425
Stay front-sight focused.

284
00:17:44.063 --> 00:17:45.932
Awful lot of firepower
Pollard's crew

285
00:17:46.065 --> 00:17:49.169
was packing today.
Not his M.O.

286
00:17:49.269 --> 00:17:51.438
He uses different tactics
for pulling off a heist

287
00:17:51.571 --> 00:17:52.905
and keeping his freedom.

288
00:17:53.039 --> 00:17:55.975
Man isn't willing to go quietly.
He made his choice.

289
00:17:56.075 --> 00:17:57.777
He got shot for it.

290
00:17:57.910 --> 00:17:59.879
Allegedly.

291
00:18:01.013 --> 00:18:02.081
I hit him.

292
00:18:02.882 --> 00:18:05.385
So in addition to your
SEAL and cowboy skills.

293
00:18:05.452 --> 00:18:07.220
you're also telepathic?

294
00:18:07.320 --> 00:18:10.022
Okay. who am I gonna
ask you about next?

295
00:18:10.089 --> 00:18:11.258
If you mention Dolly Weaver.

296
00:18:11.391 --> 00:18:13.293
you're walking home.

297
00:18:14.727 --> 00:18:17.597
Is that who has you checking
your phone every ten seconds?

298
00:18:18.598 --> 00:18:21.468
Garrett. actually.
He's not responding.

299
00:18:21.601 --> 00:18:23.736
Oh. he's probably just
sleeping it off.

300
00:18:23.803 --> 00:18:26.573
He was hitting it
pretty hard last night.

301
00:18:30.377 --> 00:18:34.614
911 reports an intruder
in a shed at 533 Marigold Road.

302
00:18:34.747 --> 00:18:36.816
That's four blocks
from the rodeo grounds.

303
00:18:37.617 --> 00:18:38.851
Told you I hit him.

304
00:18:40.220 --> 00:18:41.954
We'll see. cowboy.

305
00:19:08.648 --> 00:19:10.217
He's dead.

306
00:19:16.989 --> 00:19:18.625
That isn't Pollard.

307
00:19:28.801 --> 00:19:30.503
Dead guy Kayce and Andrea
found is Jack Manning

308
00:19:30.637 --> 00:19:33.540
from Pullman. Washington.
No priors.

309
00:19:33.673 --> 00:19:35.508
no known connection to Pollard.

310
00:19:35.642 --> 00:19:37.210
Okay. Where are we
with the rest of the crew?

311
00:19:37.344 --> 00:19:40.046
Troy Ryan. Kenny Roman.
Sam Harold.

312
00:19:40.146 --> 00:19:42.181
Ryan and Roman. both from Iowa.

313
00:19:42.282 --> 00:19:43.950
Harold from rural Michigan.

314
00:19:44.050 --> 00:19:45.852
And according to the FBI.

315
00:19:45.952 --> 00:19:48.187
none are known associates
to Pollard.

316
00:19:48.288 --> 00:19:49.556
Well. tough luck

317
00:19:49.656 --> 00:19:51.157
running into us on their
first time out with him.

318
00:19:51.224 --> 00:19:54.561
First time out anywhere.
They all have clean jackets.

319
00:19:54.694 --> 00:19:56.396
Clean jackets
don't mean clean living.

320
00:19:56.496 --> 00:19:57.930
True. but this ain't the crew

321
00:19:58.030 --> 00:19:59.699
that pulled off
the Lufthansa heist.

322
00:19:59.799 --> 00:20:01.234
Four strangers

323
00:20:01.368 --> 00:20:04.170
from out of state
with no criminal records.

324
00:20:04.271 --> 00:20:06.205
What are they doing in Montana?

325
00:20:06.339 --> 00:20:08.275
And where is Pollard
in all this?

326
00:20:08.375 --> 00:20:10.142
Could've been nearby when
you got the drop on his guys.

327
00:20:10.243 --> 00:20:11.478
slipped away.

328
00:20:11.578 --> 00:20:14.347
Or maybe he planned the job.
hired a crew

329
00:20:14.447 --> 00:20:16.215
while he stays in the shadows.

330
00:20:16.316 --> 00:20:18.351
Then who tipped us off
that he's in Bozeman?

331
00:20:18.451 --> 00:20:19.619
Wait. can we trace that tip that

332
00:20:19.719 --> 00:20:20.753
led us to Pollard
in the first place?

333
00:20:20.853 --> 00:20:22.021
It came from a burner phone.

334
00:20:22.088 --> 00:20:24.056
It's no longer pinging.

335
00:20:24.857 --> 00:20:27.360
I mean. Pollard's M.O.
has always been hands-on.

336
00:20:27.427 --> 00:20:28.795
so I know he's close by.

337
00:20:29.929 --> 00:20:32.064
We got to flip these four worlds
upside down.

338
00:20:32.164 --> 00:20:34.467
Maybe something will pop.
put us on to his whereabouts.

339
00:20:34.567 --> 00:20:37.404
And if he's the mastermind here.
then he armed these guys.

340
00:20:37.504 --> 00:20:39.339
Ballistics on the gun
might tell us a different story.

341
00:20:39.406 --> 00:20:40.807
Yeah. that's good thinking.

342
00:20:40.907 --> 00:20:42.509
Miles. Belle. you keep
digging into this crew.

343
00:20:42.609 --> 00:20:43.610
Let's get those
recovered weapons

344
00:20:43.710 --> 00:20:44.944
over to the ballistics lab.

345
00:20:56.155 --> 00:20:57.490
Where'd Kayce go. by the way?

346
00:20:57.590 --> 00:20:59.759
Said he needed to go
check on Garrett.

347
00:20:59.859 --> 00:21:01.027
Is something wrong?

348
00:21:01.093 --> 00:21:03.195
Couldn't get ahold of him.

349
00:21:06.265 --> 00:21:08.435
What is up with you
and Double G?

350
00:21:08.535 --> 00:21:09.936
He seems like a great guy.

351
00:21:10.036 --> 00:21:12.104
I thought the brotherhood
bonded you for life?

352
00:21:13.706 --> 00:21:15.842
Get these to the lab. okay?

353
00:21:16.976 --> 00:21:18.978
Oh. damn it.

354
00:21:19.078 --> 00:21:20.413
What's up?

355
00:21:20.480 --> 00:21:22.181
Look. there's. um. there's
something I forgot to do.

356
00:21:22.281 --> 00:21:23.916
Can you make this run solo?

357
00:21:23.983 --> 00:21:26.986
If it spares me your
yacht rock playlist. I got it.

358
00:21:27.086 --> 00:21:29.989
Look. and hey. make sure
they expedite the tests.

359
00:21:30.122 --> 00:21:32.091
- Okay?
- Hooyah. Senior Chief.

360
00:21:43.603 --> 00:21:45.805
Roner.

361
00:21:45.905 --> 00:21:47.139
Roner!

362
00:21:48.808 --> 00:21:51.478
Roner. I'm coming.

363
00:21:54.347 --> 00:21:55.848
Roner. I got you.

364
00:21:55.982 --> 00:21:57.817
- Hey.
- Coming. Roner.

365
00:21:57.917 --> 00:21:58.951
- Garrett.
- I'm coming.

366
00:21:59.051 --> 00:22:01.153
Hey. you're good.
Garrett. Hey.

367
00:22:01.253 --> 00:22:02.489
Get off me. Get off me.

368
00:22:02.589 --> 00:22:04.090
Get off me.

369
00:22:04.190 --> 00:22:06.559
- Garrett.
- Get off me.

370
00:22:07.927 --> 00:22:10.296
- Get off...
- Hey. Garrett.

371
00:22:10.363 --> 00:22:11.998
Garrett. you're good.
It's Coyo.

372
00:22:12.098 --> 00:22:14.667
Hey. It's Coyo. You're good.
You're good.

373
00:22:14.767 --> 00:22:18.004
Hey. hey. you're good. Hey. Hey.

374
00:22:18.104 --> 00:22:21.774
Hey. Hey. Yeah.
You're all right.

375
00:22:21.874 --> 00:22:24.243
Yeah. You're all right.

376
00:22:24.343 --> 00:22:26.979
You're all right. dude. Come on.

377
00:22:27.079 --> 00:22:29.148
You're good.

378
00:22:29.248 --> 00:22:31.384
You're good. You're good.

379
00:22:34.053 --> 00:22:35.622
Still not able to link
any of the shooters

380
00:22:35.688 --> 00:22:36.823
with Pollard or each other.

381
00:22:36.923 --> 00:22:39.258
No texts. emails. calls.

382
00:22:39.358 --> 00:22:41.060
I'm coming up empty myself.

383
00:22:41.193 --> 00:22:45.297
I can't even find evidence
that they were casing a target.

384
00:22:45.364 --> 00:22:46.866
I don't think failing Cal's

385
00:22:46.966 --> 00:22:48.701
gonna get me back
in his good graces.

386
00:22:48.801 --> 00:22:51.804
Sounds like you're at least
winning in your love life.

387
00:22:52.739 --> 00:22:54.541
- He told you about Maddie.
- Mm.

388
00:22:54.674 --> 00:22:55.975
How pissed is he?

389
00:22:56.042 --> 00:22:59.712
I wouldn't say
he's doing cartwheels over it.

390
00:23:01.981 --> 00:23:03.382
Story of my life.

391
00:23:03.516 --> 00:23:05.251
Good thing's always followed
by a bad one.

392
00:23:05.384 --> 00:23:09.255
Miles. you liked a girl.
you asked her out.

393
00:23:09.388 --> 00:23:11.290
she said yes.

394
00:23:12.158 --> 00:23:14.160
It's all good.

395
00:23:14.260 --> 00:23:16.062
No. it's not.

396
00:23:16.162 --> 00:23:20.399
My personal life's complicating
my relationship with my boss.

397
00:23:22.068 --> 00:23:23.436
Yeah.

398
00:23:23.570 --> 00:23:28.040
Well. I'm sure
it'll be awkward for a bit.

399
00:23:28.107 --> 00:23:29.876
but it'll blow over.

400
00:23:29.976 --> 00:23:34.781
Just when I started feeling like
I belonged at this job. now...

401
00:23:34.881 --> 00:23:38.651
Cal is only upset
because Maddie is into you.

402
00:23:38.751 --> 00:23:43.055
and she has been keeping him at
arm's length since he got here.

403
00:23:44.624 --> 00:23:47.460
Wait. how long have you known
Maddie's his daughter?

404
00:23:47.960 --> 00:23:49.629
Got some personal details there?

405
00:23:49.729 --> 00:23:53.365
No. I was just assuming things
aren't great with Cal

406
00:23:53.466 --> 00:23:55.835
because he had us going
to his daughter's bar

407
00:23:55.968 --> 00:23:57.504
without sharing why.

408
00:24:00.372 --> 00:24:02.809
We should get back to Pollard.

409
00:24:17.824 --> 00:24:19.559
I'll clear out now.

410
00:24:20.359 --> 00:24:21.894
Get out of your hair.

411
00:24:24.797 --> 00:24:27.033
Sorry for the trouble.

412
00:24:30.503 --> 00:24:33.540
We're all haunted by what
we did outside the wire.

413
00:24:35.041 --> 00:24:36.576
Or didn't do.

414
00:24:37.744 --> 00:24:40.279
You know. it's pretty twisted
how much more sense life makes

415
00:24:40.346 --> 00:24:43.149
in a war zone
than in the civilized world.

416
00:24:44.517 --> 00:24:47.186
I thought music
was your new purpose

417
00:24:47.286 --> 00:24:49.856
and you're out
doing what you love.

418
00:24:51.524 --> 00:24:54.594
Stopped doing what I love when
I got kicked out of the Teams.

419
00:24:56.729 --> 00:25:00.299
I used to be a part
of an elite combat unit.

420
00:25:00.399 --> 00:25:02.368
Now. I'm...

421
00:25:02.468 --> 00:25:07.439
scrounging for gigs up and down
the Honky Tonk Highway. and...

422
00:25:07.540 --> 00:25:08.975
grown tired of it.

423
00:25:09.542 --> 00:25:12.111
Man. they outed
all the quitters in BUD/S.

424
00:25:12.979 --> 00:25:14.881
You dragging
that guitar around tells me

425
00:25:14.981 --> 00:25:16.716
you're still in the fight.

426
00:25:18.317 --> 00:25:20.620
Music's my only escape.

427
00:25:20.720 --> 00:25:23.155
My only healthy one anyway.

428
00:25:23.923 --> 00:25:27.894
Yeah. when I'm on the stage.
that adrenaline. it...

429
00:25:28.027 --> 00:25:29.596
it helps me forget
about the past.

430
00:25:29.729 --> 00:25:32.431
but as soon as
the applause dies down...

431
00:25:33.733 --> 00:25:35.868
I say good night to the sun.

432
00:25:39.739 --> 00:25:42.074
Things got pretty dark
for you. huh?

433
00:25:44.911 --> 00:25:46.445
In and out of jail.

434
00:25:47.513 --> 00:25:50.817
Psych wards. rehab.
sleeping on the streets.

435
00:25:52.885 --> 00:25:55.221
That last op changed everything.

436
00:25:56.589 --> 00:25:57.890
Yeah.

437
00:25:59.091 --> 00:26:01.060
For all four of us.

438
00:26:03.896 --> 00:26:06.098
You've taken
your hits. man. but...

439
00:26:07.399 --> 00:26:09.335
you're a survivor.

440
00:26:11.203 --> 00:26:14.506
I feel like surviving's
my punishment for what I did.

441
00:26:16.275 --> 00:26:17.777
You may have a lot of demons.

442
00:26:17.877 --> 00:26:20.012
but don't go fighting
for something you didn't earn.

443
00:26:22.882 --> 00:26:25.217
We both know
who Roner's death is on.

444
00:26:27.353 --> 00:26:29.488
I'm trying to
get my head right. Coyo.

445
00:26:30.657 --> 00:26:32.324
I'm losing hope.

446
00:26:37.429 --> 00:26:40.466
I've dealt with a lot of hurt
and loss myself.

447
00:26:42.334 --> 00:26:44.436
This ranch helps.

448
00:26:45.237 --> 00:26:49.876
I may sing country.
but I ain't no cowboy.

449
00:26:49.976 --> 00:26:53.680
The healing power of nature.
that's-that's a real thing.

450
00:26:53.813 --> 00:26:57.149
Being out on the land.

451
00:26:57.283 --> 00:26:59.351
feel a part of it.

452
00:27:02.722 --> 00:27:03.923
It's been a long time

453
00:27:04.023 --> 00:27:06.192
since I felt like
I was a part of anything.

454
00:27:07.159 --> 00:27:08.627
Stay here.

455
00:27:09.461 --> 00:27:12.264
Long as you need until you

456
00:27:12.331 --> 00:27:14.834
find a path forward.

457
00:27:17.636 --> 00:27:19.972
You sure about that?

458
00:27:20.072 --> 00:27:21.674
I mean. I'm-I'm
a lot more complicated

459
00:27:21.808 --> 00:27:23.342
than that ornery horse.

460
00:27:26.846 --> 00:27:29.248
We might not be teammates
anymore.

461
00:27:30.549 --> 00:27:32.551
We're still brothers.

462
00:27:39.859 --> 00:27:41.293
I know it's a lot to take in.

463
00:27:42.094 --> 00:27:43.562
I'll loop in
a couple of specialists

464
00:27:43.696 --> 00:27:45.564
who have experience
with these kinds of cases.

465
00:27:45.664 --> 00:27:48.634
It's important
to know that you're not alone.

466
00:27:48.735 --> 00:27:51.337
Support groups can provide
a source of stability.

467
00:27:51.437 --> 00:27:53.205
especially early on...

468
00:28:17.229 --> 00:28:20.099
Turn left in 400 feet.

469
00:28:20.199 --> 00:28:24.070
Left ahead?
I already made two lefts.

470
00:28:39.185 --> 00:28:40.719
Mm. Hey.

471
00:28:40.820 --> 00:28:42.288
You didn't respond to my texts.

472
00:28:42.421 --> 00:28:44.290
Uh. I got sidetracked.

473
00:28:44.390 --> 00:28:47.259
Well. we didn't.
We located Pollard.

474
00:28:47.359 --> 00:28:48.594
Where was he hiding out?

475
00:28:48.694 --> 00:28:51.630
A jail in Las Cruces.

476
00:28:51.764 --> 00:28:53.099
New Mexico?

477
00:28:53.199 --> 00:28:56.302
Got picked up five days ago
under an alias.

478
00:28:56.402 --> 00:28:58.805
Small-town cops.
it took them a minute to realize

479
00:28:58.938 --> 00:28:59.839
they had bagged a whale.

480
00:28:59.939 --> 00:29:01.140
Why would someone tip us off

481
00:29:01.240 --> 00:29:03.442
about a fugitive
a thousand miles away?

482
00:29:03.542 --> 00:29:05.912
And Las Cruces cops say
they found nothing on Pollard

483
00:29:06.012 --> 00:29:08.881
pointing to any jobs in Montana.

484
00:29:09.715 --> 00:29:11.350
Did anything pop
on the rest of the crew?

485
00:29:11.450 --> 00:29:14.253
Still hard to figure out
what brought them here.

486
00:29:14.353 --> 00:29:18.825
and no evidence that they were
casing any spots for a heist.

487
00:29:20.092 --> 00:29:22.161
This is starting to feel
like a setup.

488
00:29:22.294 --> 00:29:25.764
Wait. did forensics get back
on the ETA with these results?

489
00:29:25.832 --> 00:29:27.233
No. nothing yet.

490
00:29:27.299 --> 00:29:29.335
Wh... I thought you and Andrea
were doing that together.

491
00:29:30.502 --> 00:29:32.638
Yeah. I to... I mean.
I told you. I got sidetracked.

492
00:29:32.738 --> 00:29:33.973
By what?

493
00:29:34.073 --> 00:29:38.310
Um... Just. uh.
get-get a sitrep from her.

494
00:29:49.588 --> 00:29:52.024
- Hey.
- Hey.

495
00:29:53.659 --> 00:29:55.794
Taking on one of those
battles you mentioned?

496
00:29:56.595 --> 00:30:00.766
Nah. I was just trying
to figure out if Pollard was.

497
00:30:00.867 --> 00:30:03.435
you know.
some kind of bait for us.

498
00:30:03.502 --> 00:30:05.437
You know?

499
00:30:05.504 --> 00:30:07.473
How's. uh. Garrett?

500
00:30:08.374 --> 00:30:11.443
He's still carrying a lot
of baggage. You were right.

501
00:30:12.644 --> 00:30:13.880
How bad?

502
00:30:14.546 --> 00:30:18.217
Sounds like he's gone Winchester
in his fight to keep going.

503
00:30:19.385 --> 00:30:21.287
And away from the chaos.
you know.

504
00:30:21.353 --> 00:30:23.489
these demons in your head.
they just

505
00:30:23.555 --> 00:30:24.991
keep grinding you down.

506
00:30:25.091 --> 00:30:26.592
especially if you don't got
teammates to lean on.

507
00:30:26.692 --> 00:30:27.894
Mm-hmm.

508
00:30:27.994 --> 00:30:30.062
And taking his bird
will do that.

509
00:30:30.162 --> 00:30:33.832
I tried everything.
everything. to avoid that.

510
00:30:35.367 --> 00:30:37.136
He's gonna stay with me
for a while.

511
00:30:37.203 --> 00:30:39.238
see if he can sort
some stuff out.

512
00:30:39.338 --> 00:30:40.706
You sure that's a good idea?

513
00:30:40.806 --> 00:30:43.075
Is "no man left behind"
not a thing for you?

514
00:30:43.209 --> 00:30:44.977
You know. he's my brother.
too. Coyo.

515
00:30:45.077 --> 00:30:48.714
And as his team leader. I feel
responsible for his struggles.

516
00:30:48.814 --> 00:30:52.084
but we both know
how combustible Double G is.

517
00:30:52.985 --> 00:30:55.254
I just don't want you
in his blast radius.

518
00:30:56.488 --> 00:30:58.690
It feels like we lost
two brothers on that op.

519
00:31:03.495 --> 00:31:04.763
- Hey.
- Hey.

520
00:31:04.863 --> 00:31:06.432
You heard back from Andrea?

521
00:31:06.565 --> 00:31:09.168
She's not answering her phone.
and the forensics lab said

522
00:31:09.268 --> 00:31:11.003
she never dropped
the weapons off.

523
00:31:11.437 --> 00:31:13.705
Miles is trying to get
a hit on her SUV.

524
00:31:13.805 --> 00:31:16.842
She should've been
there and back by now.

525
00:31:16.943 --> 00:31:19.045
Miles. what do you got?

526
00:31:19.111 --> 00:31:21.580
Sheriff found
Andrea's vehicle two miles

527
00:31:21.680 --> 00:31:23.282
- from the lab. smashed up.
- What?

528
00:31:23.415 --> 00:31:25.384
- Is she okay?
- There's blood

529
00:31:25.484 --> 00:31:27.086
in the vehicle.
but she wasn't on scene.

530
00:31:27.186 --> 00:31:28.454
What'd she hit?

531
00:31:28.587 --> 00:31:31.190
Truck hit her. broadside.
but it was also empty.

532
00:31:31.290 --> 00:31:32.591
Could be a hit-and-run.

533
00:31:32.724 --> 00:31:34.593
Did she run. too?

534
00:31:34.693 --> 00:31:37.263
Maybe she was in shock?
Wandered off.

535
00:31:37.396 --> 00:31:41.000
Or a Good Samaritan passed by
and took them all to a hospital.

536
00:31:41.100 --> 00:31:43.469
First we get ambushed
at the rodeo.

537
00:31:43.602 --> 00:31:44.937
now Andrea's missing?

538
00:31:45.071 --> 00:31:46.572
Feels coordinated.

539
00:31:46.672 --> 00:31:48.740
- DUSTWUN.
- What does that mean?

540
00:31:48.840 --> 00:31:50.442
Whereabouts unknown.

541
00:31:50.542 --> 00:31:52.544
Sheriff just sent over
traffic cam footage.

542
00:31:52.611 --> 00:31:54.580
All right.
Throw it up on the screen.

543
00:31:56.082 --> 00:31:57.950
There she is.

544
00:32:04.656 --> 00:32:06.625
That's no accident.

545
00:32:06.758 --> 00:32:08.327
Smash-and-grab.

546
00:32:08.460 --> 00:32:10.562
Classic ambush technique.

547
00:32:10.629 --> 00:32:12.364
My God.

548
00:32:13.265 --> 00:32:14.433
She's not moving.

549
00:32:14.500 --> 00:32:15.867
Yeah.

550
00:32:15.968 --> 00:32:17.636
Impact probably knocked her out.

551
00:32:19.972 --> 00:32:23.109
Okay. Okay. listen up. Hey!

552
00:32:23.175 --> 00:32:24.876
Hey. listen up!

553
00:32:25.777 --> 00:32:28.714
Deputy Marshal Andrea Cruz
has been abducted.

554
00:32:28.814 --> 00:32:30.349
So. whatever you're doing.

555
00:32:30.449 --> 00:32:32.418
getting her back
is our only priority.

556
00:32:32.484 --> 00:32:34.853
Okay? So you track her van.

557
00:32:34.953 --> 00:32:36.888
you ping her phone.
you do whatever it takes.

558
00:32:36.989 --> 00:32:39.325
Okay? No one's taking a break
till she gets back safe.

559
00:32:39.458 --> 00:32:40.792
No one. Let's go.

560
00:32:40.859 --> 00:32:42.894
Get to work!

561
00:32:44.596 --> 00:32:47.166
Hey. who the hell's
coming after us?

562
00:32:47.299 --> 00:32:49.901
Whoever it is.
it feels personal.

563
00:33:14.726 --> 00:33:18.230
Help! Help!

564
00:33:18.364 --> 00:33:20.266
Behave.

565
00:33:35.581 --> 00:33:38.016
Help! Help!

566
00:33:40.852 --> 00:33:44.056
Yell all you want.
No one's around to hear you.

567
00:33:47.626 --> 00:33:49.095
Stay there.

568
00:33:52.198 --> 00:33:53.665
Hey. Any luck
tracking her phone?

569
00:33:53.732 --> 00:33:55.134
Been trying to ping it.

570
00:33:55.234 --> 00:33:57.836
It's either turned off
or destroyed.

571
00:33:59.205 --> 00:34:01.173
Road weather cam
a few miles from the accident

572
00:34:01.240 --> 00:34:03.309
caught a cargo van
matching our BOLO.

573
00:34:03.409 --> 00:34:04.710
Okay. it's got to be
the same one.

574
00:34:04.810 --> 00:34:06.178
Got a hit on the registration.

575
00:34:06.278 --> 00:34:08.514
It's a business.
Treasure State Demolition.

576
00:34:09.281 --> 00:34:12.150
That's the first thing
that's made sense all day.

577
00:34:19.690 --> 00:34:22.994
Deputy U.S. Marshal Andrea Cruz.

578
00:34:23.929 --> 00:34:25.664
In my home.

579
00:34:27.466 --> 00:34:29.268
What an honor.

580
00:34:29.368 --> 00:34:31.969
Full force of the U.S.
government will be coming for me

581
00:34:32.103 --> 00:34:34.340
and you for breaking the law.

582
00:34:38.543 --> 00:34:40.045
Randall Clegg.

583
00:34:40.112 --> 00:34:44.116
After what your team
has done to my family.

584
00:34:44.216 --> 00:34:47.786
the only law that concerns me
is an eye for an eye.

585
00:34:52.291 --> 00:34:54.493
Stand up.

586
00:34:59.665 --> 00:35:02.734
Let's prep for a full assault
on Randall Clegg's compound.

587
00:35:04.102 --> 00:35:05.537
Would he grab Andrea
and take her

588
00:35:05.637 --> 00:35:06.938
to the first place we'd look?

589
00:35:07.005 --> 00:35:08.307
Even if she's not there.

590
00:35:08.407 --> 00:35:10.142
somebody on that property
will know something.

591
00:35:10.276 --> 00:35:13.579
What are the protocols
for an abducted U.S. Marshal?

592
00:35:13.645 --> 00:35:15.781
Tear Montana apart
till we find our teammate.

593
00:35:15.847 --> 00:35:18.950
I got a call into Gifford.
It's all hands on deck.

594
00:35:19.351 --> 00:35:21.453
What the hell is Clegg doing?

595
00:35:21.553 --> 00:35:23.021
Getting payback.

596
00:35:23.155 --> 00:35:25.191
Those zip ties we recovered
off the gunmen at the rodeo.

597
00:35:25.291 --> 00:35:26.525
they must've been meant for us.

598
00:35:26.658 --> 00:35:29.195
Going after Kayce's job
is one thing.

599
00:35:29.295 --> 00:35:33.131
but kidnapping a U.S. Marshal?
Why now?

600
00:35:33.199 --> 00:35:34.833
His business went bust.

601
00:35:34.933 --> 00:35:36.502
He lost the rare earth mine
demo contracts

602
00:35:36.635 --> 00:35:38.870
after his sons
shot up Broken Rock.

603
00:35:38.970 --> 00:35:41.540
With one son dead and another
one facing life in prison.

604
00:35:41.673 --> 00:35:42.674
he's got nothing to lose.

605
00:35:45.177 --> 00:35:46.612
Does an assault

606
00:35:46.712 --> 00:35:48.214
put Andrea at risk
if he's doing this to negotiate?

607
00:35:48.647 --> 00:35:50.716
Clegg knows
he's crossed the Rubicon.

608
00:35:50.816 --> 00:35:52.518
He is ready to go out
on his shield.

609
00:35:52.618 --> 00:35:53.852
Making himself a martyr

610
00:35:53.985 --> 00:35:55.987
certainly helps gain sympathy
for his son.

611
00:35:56.054 --> 00:35:58.857
I'm happy to oblige him.

612
00:36:01.560 --> 00:36:04.196
You know. I've been teammates
with Andrea for months now.

613
00:36:04.330 --> 00:36:07.199
I don't even know who to notify
as her next of kin.

614
00:36:09.134 --> 00:36:11.270
I think she said her mom
was back in New York.

615
00:36:12.838 --> 00:36:17.008
Right now. we're all
the family she's got.

616
00:36:17.108 --> 00:36:18.944
so let's get her home.

617
00:36:49.541 --> 00:36:51.377
What is this?

618
00:36:52.578 --> 00:36:54.680
A man standing his ground.

619
00:37:08.093 --> 00:37:10.629
This isn't a negotiation.

620
00:37:12.531 --> 00:37:17.102
Bit by bit. I've watched
the life sucked from this land

621
00:37:17.202 --> 00:37:21.440
by faraway bureaucrats
who care nothing for it.

622
00:37:22.240 --> 00:37:24.576
I've seen the blood of my kin

623
00:37:24.676 --> 00:37:27.078
spilled by their puppets.

624
00:37:28.447 --> 00:37:32.718
You all take and take and take

625
00:37:32.818 --> 00:37:36.087
till there's nothing left
but a desert.

626
00:37:36.922 --> 00:37:39.224
It has been too dry

627
00:37:39.325 --> 00:37:42.628
for too long around here.

628
00:37:53.539 --> 00:37:55.707
And what are you in all that?

629
00:37:59.811 --> 00:38:01.980
A spark.

630
00:38:06.852 --> 00:38:09.688
It's time to burn
the land clean.

631
00:38:23.435 --> 00:38:25.404
Why was Andrea alone
when she got grabbed?

632
00:38:26.705 --> 00:38:28.374
It was a routine run.

633
00:38:28.474 --> 00:38:30.008
I didn't know we'd be
in Clegg's crosshairs.

634
00:38:30.108 --> 00:38:32.544
Belle says you were
supposed to go with her.

635
00:38:32.678 --> 00:38:33.979
Yeah. and I would've sent you.
but you

636
00:38:34.045 --> 00:38:35.013
were more worried
about your old teammate

637
00:38:35.146 --> 00:38:36.448
than the ones you got now.

638
00:38:38.684 --> 00:38:40.819
Look. man. Roner. Double G.

639
00:38:40.886 --> 00:38:42.554
that is the third rail
in our friendship.

640
00:38:42.654 --> 00:38:44.189
but the only way Drea's
gonna get out of this

641
00:38:44.322 --> 00:38:46.692
is if we are pulling
in the same direction.

642
00:38:52.097 --> 00:38:55.401
It's eerie. though. 'cause the
last thing Drea said to me...

643
00:38:56.368 --> 00:38:58.604
was. "Hooyah. Senior Chief."

644
00:39:01.373 --> 00:39:03.308
Garrett shows up
and here we are again.

645
00:39:03.409 --> 00:39:05.577
got another teammate
behind enemy lines.

646
00:39:07.546 --> 00:39:09.915
Let's hope this one
turns out better.

647
00:39:19.858 --> 00:39:21.727
This can't be
how Andrea goes out.

648
00:39:21.827 --> 00:39:22.994
Told you.
something good happens.

649
00:39:23.061 --> 00:39:25.431
something bad always follows.

650
00:39:27.933 --> 00:39:29.601
Coming up on the property line.

651
00:39:29.735 --> 00:39:31.302
There's an
access road a few miles past

652
00:39:31.403 --> 00:39:33.338
the main entrance
to the Clegg compound.

653
00:39:33.405 --> 00:39:36.207
- We can jock up there.
- Copy that.

654
00:39:44.950 --> 00:39:46.752
No signs of activity.

655
00:39:46.852 --> 00:39:48.587
- How far out is backup?
- Like an hour out.

656
00:39:48.687 --> 00:39:50.456
- but we can't wait for them.
- With any luck.

657
00:39:50.589 --> 00:39:52.658
we pull this together faster
than Clegg expected.

658
00:39:52.758 --> 00:39:53.959
Yeah. we catch them off guard.

659
00:39:54.092 --> 00:39:55.527
that's our best
tactical advantage.

660
00:39:55.627 --> 00:39:57.563
Okay. look.
we're gonna proceed on foot.

661
00:39:57.629 --> 00:39:59.030
fast and quiet.

662
00:39:59.130 --> 00:40:00.766
Belle. Miles. you're gonna take
the left flank.

663
00:40:00.899 --> 00:40:02.300
Kayce and I will take the right.
and when we get to the target.

664
00:40:02.434 --> 00:40:04.770
we're gonna clear
that main house first.

665
00:40:04.870 --> 00:40:06.872
I know we're all out for blood
right now. all right?

666
00:40:06.938 --> 00:40:08.740
But remember.
this is a hostage rescue. okay?

667
00:40:08.840 --> 00:40:11.643
So careful where you send
your rounds downrange.

668
00:40:11.743 --> 00:40:13.779
- Let's get our girl back.
- Let's go.

669
00:41:17.576 --> 00:41:19.044
Contact front!

670
00:41:22.614 --> 00:41:24.249
Down. down. down.

671
00:41:26.785 --> 00:41:28.720
We need fire on that bunker!

672
00:41:35.226 --> 00:41:36.962
Contact right!

673
00:41:37.062 --> 00:41:38.897
They were expecting us.

674
00:41:46.304 --> 00:41:48.139
Clegg went
and got himself an army.

675
00:41:55.513 --> 00:41:57.415
More shooters in the barn.

676
00:41:57.549 --> 00:41:59.050
They're gonna overrun us.

677
00:42:00.185 --> 00:42:01.620
Watch the flank.

678
00:42:04.590 --> 00:42:06.524
We got to get off the X.
